.TH SHOREWALL-NFT-RAWNAT 5 "2026-04-20" "shorewall-nft 1.10.0" "File Formats"
.SH NAME
shorewall\-nft\-rawnat \- raw (pre-conntrack) NAT rules for shorewall-nft
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.I rawnat
file defines NAT rules that are applied in the
.B prerouting raw
chain, before conntrack.  Use this for NAT that must occur before conntrack
records the connection (e.g. for traffic that must not be tracked).

.SH FILE FORMAT
Location:
.I /etc/shorewall/rawnat
(or inside a merged
.IR /etc/shorewall46/ ).
.PP
Columns are whitespace-separated.  Lines beginning with
.B #
are comments.

.TS
l l l.
Column	Required	Description
_
ACTION	yes	DNAT or SNAT
SOURCE	yes	Source address or CIDR (or - for any)
DEST	yes	Destination address or CIDR (or - for any)
PROTO	no	Protocol filter
DPORT	no	Destination port filter
SPORT	no	Source port filter
USER	no	User/group match
.TE

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Raw DNAT — redirect inbound traffic before conntrack:
.RS
.nf
#ACTION  SOURCE          DEST           PROTO  DPORT
DNAT     -               203.0.113.10   tcp    80    198.51.100.20:8080
.fi
.RE
.PP
Raw SNAT — rewrite source before conntrack:
.RS
.nf
SNAT     192.168.1.100   -              -      -     203.0.113.5
.fi
.RE

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR shorewall\-nft (8),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-masq (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-rules (5),
.BR shorewall\-nft\-notrack (5)

